<TITLE> Iraq minibus bomb kills six </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DIWANIYA, Iraq, Sep 28, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A bomb planted on a minibus south of Baghdad killed six people and wounded two others on Monday, Iraqi police said. The bomb was planted on the rear part of the vehicle, which was traveling in an area just north of Diwaniya, 150 km (95 miles) south of Baghdad. All those killed in the attack, which took place in the small town of Saniya, were passengers, police said. Violence has fallen sharply in Iraq since the height of the sectarian killing unleashed by the 2003 US-led invasion. This month, at the end of Ramadan, Iraqis enjoyed the most tranquil Eid al-Fitr holiday in years. Still, roadside bombs, shootings and suicide attacks remain common, raising questions about local security forces' ability to keep Iraqis safe as US troops prepare to withdraw by 2012. Increasingly common are attacks using so-called 'sticky bombs', explosives that are planted on cars using magnets or other me
